  "comment": "ALL-FAMILIES-TOGETHER palette (AL 2026-07-12): the ζ₂₄ union of star24 (regular {3,4,6,8,12} + Myers in-ring star species) and composite-convex (Family A decomposable + Family B non-decomposable composites, angles rescaled from the D=12 spec to D=24 units, i.e. doubled). This puts regular, star and composable/non-composable tiles in ONE alphabet so k-uniform tilings mixing all three families are enumerated together. NOT a completeness target: composites admit multiple dissections (decomposition ambiguity), so counts are over the tile alphabet, not all-and-only geometric tilings; do not compare to A068599. maxValence=12 is Myers' in-ring bound (a cap — logged, not silent). Star sub-families star18/star20 (9-fold / 5-fold) are EXCLUDED by construction: their direction systems (ζ₁₈ / ζ₂₀) are incommensurable with ζ₂₄, so they cannot share this periodic lattice.",
